# SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
# Bustfile — failure mode contractile for 688 Attack Hub
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell (hyperpolymath)
#
# Every declared failure mode should have a recovery path. Status moves:
#   declared → drilled (probe run) → verified (recovery confirmed)
#   or → failing (recovery broken)
#
# This repo has had no real incidents yet — unlike f19-stealth-glider's
# Bustfile (which records genuine occurrences), everything below is
# `declared`, not `verified`. Update status to `verified` only after the
# failure genuinely happens and the recovery is genuinely exercised.

@abstract:
Failure modes specific to 688 Attack Hub: a single-file browser game with a
GitHub Pages deployment and no build step. Most realistic failure modes are
CI/publication issues, not gameplay bugs.
@end

## Failure Modes

### pages-artifact-startup-failure
- class: ci_cd
- description: pages.yml fails at startup because an action calls an unpinned transitive action (the actions/upload-pages-artifact problem f19-stealth-glider already hit)
- recovery: pages.yml already hand-packs the artifact instead of using actions/upload-pages-artifact — see the comment block at the top of that file
- expected_recovery_time_seconds: 300
- status: declared
- notes: If this recurs, check every `uses:` for a transitive unpinned action, not just the top-level ones

### published-bundle-diverges-from-committed-file
- class: supply_chain
- description: The file served from GitHub Pages differs from the file in the repository
- recovery: re-run pages.yml; verify with `diff <(curl -s https://metadatastician.github.io/688-attack-hub/) 688-attack-hub.html`
- expected_recovery_time_seconds: 120
- status: declared

### network-primitive-reintroduced
- class: design_invariant
- description: A future change adds a fetch/eval/exec primitive to the game, falsifying AUDIT.adoc's central claim
- recovery: ci.yml's integrity job fails the build automatically; revert the change
- expected_recovery_time_seconds: 60
- status: declared
- notes: This is the one failure mode this repo actually has automated detection for

### clade-identity-copied-from-template
- class: metadata
- description: CLADE.a2ml's UUID/canonical-name accidentally reverts to rsr-template-repo's own identity (a proven estate-wide bug — see that file's own CLADE.a2ml)
- recovery: recompute with `uuidgen --sha1 --namespace @url --name "github.com/metadatastician/688-attack-hub"` and confirm it matches the value already in the file
- expected_recovery_time_seconds: 60
- status: declared
